Java `File` class is an example of the [Composite Design Pattern][1], so you have to actually ask the instance if it&#39;s a file: `isFile()` or if it&#39;s a directory `isDirectory()`.

If you want to count directories, and you&#39;re using Java 8. [`Files.find`][2] function, can do the same thing in a more concise manner (practically one-liner):

